The paper discusses techniques for improving the correctness and efficiency of untyped languages, specifically in the context of the Ciao assertion language and combined static/dynamic checking framework. This suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of module systems to improve static analysis, which falls under logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of overhead in run-time checking, which could fall under computer systems and networking (cs.SY) or machine learning (cs.LG) depending on the specific techniques used.
